WEBVTT

00:03.706 --> 00:06.869
No, seriously, I think I've finally figured out
my problem with women.

00:07.110 --> 00:10.637
The capybara is the largest member
of the rodent family.

00:10.847 --> 00:13.008
What does that have to do
with me and women?

00:13.216 --> 00:15.047
Nothing, it was a desperate attempt...

00:15.218 --> 00:18.210
...to introduce
an alternate topic of conversation.

00:18.388 --> 00:20.618
My problem
is I don't project confidence.

00:20.790 --> 00:24.282
So I decided that the next time I meet
a woman I think is attractive...

00:24.460 --> 00:26.792
...rather than holding back
and being cautious...

00:26.963 --> 00:28.897
...I'll assume
the mantle of self-assurance.

00:29.198 --> 00:31.530
Oh, yeah? What does that look like?

00:34.837 --> 00:36.327
Hi.

00:36.873 --> 00:38.670
I'm Leonard.

00:39.509 --> 00:40.999
And you are beautiful.

00:41.177 --> 00:44.704
You pop, sparkle and buzz electric.

00:44.881 --> 00:50.649
I'm gonna pick you up at 8,
show you a night you will never forget.

00:51.254 --> 00:53.484
Where are we going?

00:57.260 --> 01:01.026
Good news, I made it onto the team
for the new Defense Department...

01:01.197 --> 01:04.496
...laser-equipped surveillance satellite.
- Excuse me.

01:04.667 --> 01:08.000
If we're changing topics, I believe
I have first dibs with capybara...

01:08.171 --> 01:11.038
...a rodent the size of a baby hippo.

01:12.075 --> 01:14.566
- Congratulations, Howard.
HOWARD: Thanks.

01:14.777 --> 01:16.938
Listen,
I have to get a security clearance...

01:17.146 --> 01:19.671
...so you guys might be hearing
from the FBI.

01:19.849 --> 01:22.443
Whoa, whoa, whoa.
I don't want to speak to the FBI.

01:23.252 --> 01:26.517
- Why not?
- I'm brown and I talk funny.

01:26.723 --> 01:28.953
They're just doing
a background check on me.

01:29.192 --> 01:33.458
It doesn't matter, they'll find a reason to
give me a one-way ticket to Gandhiville.

01:33.663 --> 01:36.029
By the way, when I say that,
it's not offensive.

01:36.799 --> 01:38.027
Don't be ridiculous, Raj.

01:38.201 --> 01:40.032
- You're here legally.
- Nobody cares.

01:40.203 --> 01:42.831
You know how long it's been
since I got through airport security...

01:43.005 --> 01:45.132
...without being given a colonoscopy?

01:45.308 --> 01:49.540
You know, I try very hard to make our
lunch hours educational and informative.

01:49.712 --> 01:54.411
But your insistence on talking about
your own lives stymies me at every turn.

01:54.984 --> 01:57.214
Fine, Sheldon,
tell us about your giant rodents.

01:57.387 --> 02:01.380
No. You squandered your time with me
and the moment has now passed.

02:01.557 --> 02:03.047
Feast on your disappointment...

02:03.226 --> 02:06.627
...much as the capybara
feasts on its own waste.

02:37.393 --> 02:39.691
Oh, Bella, don't you see?

02:39.862 --> 02:43.263
Edward's only pushing you away
because he loves you.

02:43.800 --> 02:44.824
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

02:45.067 --> 02:46.091
Coming.

02:46.269 --> 02:47.293
[CLEARS THROAT]

02:51.073 --> 02:52.131
Dr. Koothrappali?

02:54.644 --> 02:58.011
I'm Special Agent Page, FBI.
May I come in?

03:00.416 --> 03:03.783
I'd like to talk to you
about Howard Wolowitz.

03:03.953 --> 03:05.921
Ah, thank you.

03:06.088 --> 03:09.216
All right. Well, how long have you known
Mr. Wolowitz?

03:31.314 --> 03:34.181
- Rum cake?
- No, thanks.

03:34.383 --> 03:36.317
Now, about Mr. Wolowitz.

03:36.486 --> 03:37.748
Seven years.

03:37.920 --> 03:39.410
I see.

03:42.091 --> 03:44.616
I'm in this country legally, you know.

03:44.794 --> 03:46.159
I'm sure you are.

03:46.329 --> 03:47.557
Now, to your knowledge...

03:47.730 --> 03:49.823
...has Mr. Wolowitz
ever committed a crime?

03:50.066 --> 03:51.090
Of course not.

03:51.267 --> 03:52.598
I'm here on an H1 B visa...

03:52.768 --> 03:56.169
...which means I can't be associated
with crime or criminal activity...

03:56.339 --> 03:57.567
...and I'm not.

03:57.740 --> 03:58.798
Good.

03:58.975 --> 04:01.967
To your knowledge, does Mr. Wolowitz
have any foreign contacts?

04:02.144 --> 04:04.078
No, just me.

04:04.347 --> 04:05.837
Oh, there it is.

04:06.015 --> 04:07.846
Here comes the cavity search.

04:08.718 --> 04:10.652
- Excuse me?
- Please don't send me back to India.

04:10.820 --> 04:14.312
It's so crowded. It's like the whole
country is one endless Comic-Con...

04:14.490 --> 04:19.223
...except everybody's wearing
the same costume: Indian Guy.

04:19.428 --> 04:21.362
- Dr. Koothrappali...
- I love this country.

04:21.597 --> 04:25.533
The baseball, the freedom,
the rampant morbid obesity.

04:25.735 --> 04:29.466
From California to the New York island,
I'm a real Yankee Doodle boy.

04:29.639 --> 04:30.970
Dr. Koothrappali, please.

04:31.173 --> 04:33.471
[SINGING]
My country 'tis of thee

04:33.643 --> 04:36.510
Da-da-da liberty

04:36.746 --> 04:39.476
It's really great

04:41.017 --> 04:43.508
So when Howard said
the FBI would be contacting me...

04:43.686 --> 04:45.381
...I was expecting Mulder.

04:46.322 --> 04:48.756
Glad to see I got Scully, ha, ha.

04:48.958 --> 04:51.256
- Who?
- Mulder and Scully.

04:52.194 --> 04:53.821
X-Files.

04:54.330 --> 04:56.423
"The truth is out there." Never mind.

04:56.599 --> 04:59.500
Uh, so, what would you like to know?

05:00.336 --> 05:03.169
You work with Mr. Wolowitz
here at the university, correct?

05:03.339 --> 05:05.569
Yes. Of course,
we're in different departments.

05:05.775 --> 05:08.539
He's an engineer
and I'm an experimental physicist.

05:08.711 --> 05:10.736
You know, one of those guys
who examines...

05:10.913 --> 05:13.006
...the building blocks of creation
and says:

05:13.182 --> 05:15.412
"Hello, maker of the universe.

05:16.385 --> 05:18.182
I see what you did there.

05:18.354 --> 05:19.981
Good one."

05:20.189 --> 05:21.417
Right.

05:21.591 --> 05:24.924
Now, how would you characterize
your relationship with Mr. Wolowitz?

05:25.795 --> 05:27.092
Good.

05:27.597 --> 05:29.724
It's a good relationship.

05:29.899 --> 05:32.925
Of course, most of my relationships
are good, you know.

05:33.169 --> 05:36.263
Probably because I exude confidence.

05:36.439 --> 05:38.304
People are drawn to that, you know?

05:38.541 --> 05:39.565
Mm.

05:40.376 --> 05:41.934
Confidence, not exuding.

05:44.313 --> 05:46.941
Do you know of any groups
Mr. Wolowitz is a member of?

05:47.116 --> 05:49.607
You are beautiful, you know that?

05:50.252 --> 05:54.313
You pop, sparkle and buzz electric.

05:56.425 --> 05:58.620
I'm gonna pick you up at 8.

05:58.828 --> 06:02.025
Show you a night
you will never forget.

06:02.765 --> 06:03.959
Sounds great.

06:04.734 --> 06:06.224
Really?

06:06.936 --> 06:08.028
Yeah.

06:08.204 --> 06:11.731
Can my 6'2" Navy SEAL husband
come with us?

06:13.209 --> 06:17.839
Is that...? Oh, my, I didn't see the ring
with my glasses off so...

06:18.047 --> 06:19.480
Look at that, I'm starting to exude.

06:19.649 --> 06:21.276
[CHUCKLES]

06:22.785 --> 06:23.809
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

06:23.986 --> 06:27.387
LEONARD: Wanna get that?
- Not particularly.

06:28.724 --> 06:31.784
- Could you get that?
- I suppose I could if I were asked.

06:31.961 --> 06:32.985
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

06:33.162 --> 06:36.962
- Would you please get that?
- Well, of course.

06:38.434 --> 06:41.597
Why do you have to make things
so complicated?

06:43.072 --> 06:44.767
- Dr. Cooper?
- Yes.

06:44.974 --> 06:47.875
I'm Special Agent Page, FBI.

06:50.646 --> 06:54.377
You say you're Special Agent Page,
FBI.

06:54.583 --> 06:56.244
Here's my ID.

06:56.419 --> 07:01.152
And here is my Justice League
membership card.

07:03.325 --> 07:05.452
But that doesn't prove
I know Batman.

07:06.796 --> 07:10.197
I just wanna ask you a few questions
about Howard Wolowitz.

07:10.833 --> 07:13.427
Oh. Well, all right.

07:13.969 --> 07:16.267
I doubt anyone would risk
the stiff penalties...

07:16.439 --> 07:18.930
...for impersonating a federal officer
just to ask questions...

07:19.108 --> 07:23.044
...about a minor league engineer
with an unresolved Oedipal complex.

07:24.280 --> 07:28.046
- Thank you.
- For the record, I truly support the FBI...

07:28.217 --> 07:31.209
...in the mission
which is expressed through their motto.

07:31.454 --> 07:33.922
Fidelity, bravery, integrity?

07:34.123 --> 07:36.023
Correct. Now to business.

07:36.659 --> 07:40.823
Eighteen years ago,
I sent the FBI Crime Lab samples...

07:40.996 --> 07:44.693
...from a bag of excrement that had
been lit on fire on my front porch...

07:46.802 --> 07:50.238
...for fingerprinting and DNA analysis.

07:50.439 --> 07:52.339
Why haven't I heard back yet?

07:52.842 --> 07:56.801
Well, the FBI Crime Lab
does have a lot on its plate.

07:57.012 --> 08:00.539
That's of little comfort to a nation
attempting to scrape burning feces...

08:00.716 --> 08:02.081
...off its shoes.

08:02.818 --> 08:05.252
Would you mind
if we talked about Mr. Wolowitz now?

08:05.888 --> 08:08.049
A little, but go on.

08:08.224 --> 08:09.555
Thank you.

08:09.725 --> 08:11.955
Would you characterize him
as responsible?

08:13.529 --> 08:15.724
I'm going to answer that
with a visual aid.

08:17.700 --> 08:22.262
This is my nine-disc complete
Lord of the Rings trilogy Blu-ray set.

08:22.505 --> 08:24.268
Mr. Wolowitz borrowed it...

08:24.473 --> 08:28.739
...damaged plastic retention
hub number three...

08:32.481 --> 08:35.211
...and then returned it to me
hoping I wouldn't notice.

08:35.384 --> 08:38.979
Would you characterize that
as responsible?

08:39.188 --> 08:41.884
That's really not the sort of thing
we're interested in.

08:42.792 --> 08:46.728
- You heard me say Blu-ray, right?
- I did.

08:47.563 --> 08:50.293
Very well,
would you be interested in knowing...

08:50.499 --> 08:54.265
...that Mr. Wolowitz once snuck
onto my "World of Warcraft" account...

08:54.436 --> 08:57.234
...and changed the name
of a certain level-80 warlock...

08:57.406 --> 09:00.375
...from "Sheldor" to "Smeldor"?

09:00.943 --> 09:04.140
I'm afraid not. Is there anything else?

09:04.380 --> 09:06.541
Anything else?
Where would you like to start?

09:06.715 --> 09:09.775
He refuses to pay fines when
he's overdue with books I lend him...

09:09.952 --> 09:13.046
...he crashed the Mars Rover
while attempting to impress a woman.

09:13.255 --> 09:15.951
He recommended that I go see
the third Matrix movie...

09:16.125 --> 09:19.959
...because it was, and I quote,
"Just as good as the first one."

09:20.796 --> 09:24.061
If that's not irresponsible,
I don't know what is.

09:24.266 --> 09:25.824
The Mars Rover?

09:32.107 --> 09:34.541
- Did I say Mars Rover?
- You did.

09:35.110 --> 09:37.169
That was actually
a poorly-chosen example...

09:37.346 --> 09:39.610
...as it had nothing to do with me.

09:39.815 --> 09:43.615
- Yes, well, let's talk about it anyway.
- I don't want to.

09:44.787 --> 09:47.278
Not that my disinclination
to discuss the topic...

09:47.456 --> 09:50.323
...should be interpreted as evidence
of Howard Wolowitz's culpability...

09:50.492 --> 09:53.620
...in the destruction of government
property worth millions of dollars.

09:53.829 --> 09:56.491
Thank you, Dr. Cooper.
I think I have all I need.

09:56.699 --> 09:58.792
Oh, good.

09:58.968 --> 10:02.870
I was afraid you were going to fixate
on that Mars Rover incident.

10:08.210 --> 10:09.643
Hey, buddies.

10:09.812 --> 10:13.304
Guess who didn't get security clearance
to work on the giant space laser?

10:13.482 --> 10:16.212
- What happened?
- The background interviews didn't go well.

10:16.452 --> 10:19.080
You guys wouldn't know anything
about that, would you?

10:21.223 --> 10:24.715
Well, actually, I may have gotten
a little tipsy when I talked to her.

10:26.195 --> 10:27.890
And I may have hit on her a little bit.

10:28.063 --> 10:29.155
[HOWARD SCOFFS]

10:29.331 --> 10:31.959
And I may have thrown up rum cake
on her shoes.

10:33.469 --> 10:36.666
I see. Well, it's good to know
when I need you guys...

10:36.872 --> 10:40.535
...I can always count on you
to step up and ruin everything.

10:42.678 --> 10:44.669
- I feel awful.
- Me too.

10:44.880 --> 10:48.043
I thought if anyone was gonna
screw things up for Howard...

10:48.217 --> 10:49.844
...it'd be Sheldon.

10:50.386 --> 10:54.015
Well, your expectations
have been subverted.

10:54.256 --> 10:55.348
Ha, ha.

11:03.232 --> 11:04.859
What are you doing up?

11:05.067 --> 11:07.001
Sleep eludes me, Leonard.

11:07.202 --> 11:08.328
Really?

11:08.504 --> 11:10.904
Maybe sleep has met you before.

11:11.507 --> 11:14.169
Mockery? That's all you have to offer?

11:14.376 --> 11:16.776
- I'm sorry. Why can't you sleep?
- Who knows?

11:16.946 --> 11:19.574
I haven't watched
any scary movies recently.

11:19.748 --> 11:22.342
I'm no longer obsessing
over why the predicted mass...

11:22.518 --> 11:26.249
...of the quantum vacuum has little
effect on the expansion of the universe.

11:26.422 --> 11:29.858
And it's been weeks since I took
that accidental sip of Red Bull.

11:30.693 --> 11:33.127
Did something happen today
that's bothering you?

11:33.362 --> 11:37.298
Well, I did mention the Mars Rover
incident to that FBI agent...

11:37.466 --> 11:40.026
...and probably cost Howard
his security clearance.

11:40.235 --> 11:43.068
- What?
- Yeah, but why should that keep me up?

11:43.706 --> 11:45.196
Because you feel guilty?

11:45.975 --> 11:47.465
Interesting.

11:47.643 --> 11:51.704
So you're saying my insomnia
is caused by a guilty conscience.

11:51.914 --> 11:54.781
Actually, you don't have insomnia.
You're sleeping now.

11:54.984 --> 11:58.044
- Excuse me?
- You're having a guilt-ridden dream.

11:58.253 --> 12:00.744
Do you have any evidence
to support that hypothesis?

12:00.956 --> 12:03.254
How about that Gorn
sitting on the couch?

12:07.262 --> 12:09.924
That seems fairly conclusive.

12:10.132 --> 12:12.965
No, Gorn, no.

12:13.669 --> 12:16.069
That's where I sit.

12:17.973 --> 12:20.737
Thank you for agreeing to see me,
Agent Page.

12:20.943 --> 12:24.640
Thank you for filing a complaint
with my superior, Dr. Cooper.

12:25.914 --> 12:29.247
I understand you wanna recant
your statement about Howard Wolowitz.

12:29.451 --> 12:32.249
- Yes.
- Was your statement untrue?

12:32.421 --> 12:33.513
No.

12:34.590 --> 12:36.751
Then I'm afraid you can't withdraw it.

12:36.959 --> 12:40.918
I'm sorry,
I don't recall you saying no backsies.

12:42.398 --> 12:43.763
Is there anything else?

12:43.966 --> 12:46.526
Yes, I'd like to offer
a laudatory statement...

12:46.702 --> 12:50.331
...about Howard's many excellent
qualities I believe will tip the scales...

12:50.506 --> 12:53.339
...back in his favor. Ahem.
"Howard Joel Wolowitz.

12:53.509 --> 12:56.945
H is for honesty,
of which he has much.

12:57.112 --> 12:59.603
O is for outstanding, which he is such.

12:59.782 --> 13:02.307
W is for witty, he's quick with a joke.

13:02.484 --> 13:04.452
A is for artistic, his ability..."

13:04.653 --> 13:07.451
I'm sorry, Dr. Cooper,
this matter is already closed.

13:07.656 --> 13:10.523
But I still have "ard Joel Wolowitz"
left to go.

13:11.026 --> 13:12.653
It's closed.

13:14.463 --> 13:17.125
I don't understand why you people
are picking on my friend Howard...

13:17.332 --> 13:19.823
...when there are much more serious
security threats to pursue.

13:20.002 --> 13:21.970
For instance,
when I first met Leonard...

13:22.137 --> 13:25.868
...he was on the verge of giving away
rocket secrets to a North Korean spy...

13:26.041 --> 13:28.737
...and not one agent
ever investigated that.

13:29.178 --> 13:31.669
This is Leonard Hofstadter?

13:32.514 --> 13:35.972
No, it's a different Leonard.
He's Chinese, red hair, six fingers.

13:36.151 --> 13:37.175
Goodbye.

13:41.023 --> 13:43.583
Raj, have you seen Howard?

13:43.826 --> 13:45.691
I think he's eating lunch.

13:45.894 --> 13:48.362
Uh, Sheldon, I want you to meet
Neil DeGrasse Tyson...

13:48.530 --> 13:50.293
...from the Hayden Planetarium
in New York.

13:50.466 --> 13:52.900
I'm quite familiar with Dr. Tyson.

13:53.068 --> 13:56.663
He's responsible for the demotion
of Pluto from planetary status.

13:56.839 --> 13:58.170
I liked Pluto...

13:59.475 --> 14:03.536
...ergo, I do not like you.
- But I actually didn't demote Pluto.

14:03.712 --> 14:06.374
That was a vote of
the International Astronomical Union.

14:06.548 --> 14:11.212
If ifs and buts were candy and nuts,
we'd all have a merry Christmas.

14:12.054 --> 14:13.385
Think about that, Dr. Tyson.

14:15.724 --> 14:17.555
That the guy you
were telling me about?

14:17.726 --> 14:19.057
Oh, yeah.

14:21.263 --> 14:26.394
Howard, the person at fault for you
not getting a security clearance is me.

14:27.202 --> 14:29.932
- You?
- Yes, but before you get upset...

14:30.105 --> 14:33.233
...I want you to know I went to the FBI
and retracted my statement.

14:33.775 --> 14:35.800
And they were okay with that?

14:36.011 --> 14:37.808
No. If anything, I made it worse.

14:38.814 --> 14:41.806
In any case,
I have been riddled with guilt...

14:42.017 --> 14:44.281
...which is causing
Gorn-infested REM sleep.

14:44.453 --> 14:50.119
- So I'm here now to say I'm sorry.
- Are you kidding me?

14:50.292 --> 14:52.590
You've set my career back
at least two years...

14:52.761 --> 14:55.628
...and you think you can make it right
with "I'm sorry"?

14:55.797 --> 14:57.389
Yes.

14:57.599 --> 14:59.089
I followed the social protocol.

14:59.268 --> 15:01.736
I attempted to right the wrong
and when I failed...

15:01.904 --> 15:05.806
...I delivered a heartfelt apology.
Now, you say "apology accepted"...

15:05.974 --> 15:09.273
...and I will offer you
a one-time-only high five.

15:10.846 --> 15:12.746
Your apology is not accepted.

15:13.415 --> 15:15.849
You're tricking me. It really is, isn't it?

15:16.051 --> 15:18.451
Leave me alone, Sheldon.

15:20.556 --> 15:22.421
Dr. Cooper,
I just wanted you to know...

15:22.591 --> 15:25.856
...Iâ€™m sorry for the role I played
in the Pluto matter.

15:26.061 --> 15:27.756
Oh, shut up.

15:32.334 --> 15:33.995
- Sheldon?
- Hello.

15:34.169 --> 15:35.193
[PENNY CHUCKLES]

15:35.370 --> 15:36.962
What are you doing here?

15:37.139 --> 15:38.163
I have troubles, Penny.

15:38.340 --> 15:39.364
[SIGHS]

15:39.541 --> 15:42.840
I've come to pour them out to
the sympathetic ear of the local barkeep.

15:43.612 --> 15:46.843
You know, they have a really nice bar
over at the Olive Garden.

15:47.382 --> 15:51.284
I don't like the Olive Garden.
They treat me like family.

15:53.822 --> 15:56.518
- Okay, Sheldon, what can I get you?
- Alcohol.

15:57.359 --> 16:01.125
- Could you be a little more specific?
- Ethyl alcohol.

16:01.296 --> 16:02.627
Forty milliliters.

16:03.098 --> 16:05.123
I'm sorry, honey,
I don't know milliliters.

16:05.300 --> 16:08.360
Ah. Blame President James Jimmy Carter.

16:08.537 --> 16:11.995
He started America on a path
to the metric system but then just gave up.

16:12.174 --> 16:13.198
[SCOFFS]

16:13.375 --> 16:15.673
He wonders
why he was a one-term president.

16:16.511 --> 16:19.105
- Would you say that's 40 milliliters?
- More or less.

16:19.314 --> 16:20.338
Great.

16:22.551 --> 16:23.609
Now where were we?

16:23.819 --> 16:26.583
I believe you were about to ask me
to choose a cocktail.

16:26.755 --> 16:29.986
Fortunately,
thanks to computer-savvy alcoholics...

16:30.158 --> 16:32.251
...there's an app for that.

16:32.861 --> 16:36.228
Let's see. Harvey Wallbanger. Eh.

16:36.398 --> 16:38.332
Sex on the Beach. I hardly think so.

16:39.668 --> 16:43.160
Rob Roy, Silk Slipper, Mad Hatter.

16:43.338 --> 16:44.396
Ooh.

16:44.573 --> 16:48.031
- I'll have a Rosewater Rickey.
- A what?

16:48.243 --> 16:50.768
"You'll need pitted,
brandied cherries, gin...

16:51.013 --> 16:54.039
...rosewater, Angostura bitters
and over-proofed rum.

16:54.216 --> 16:56.548
Now first,
dust the cherries with sugar...

16:56.718 --> 16:59.414
...then spray them
with a mixture of rum and bitters.

16:59.588 --> 17:03.456
- Then ignite the rum..."
- Here you go, one Rosewater Rickey.

17:03.692 --> 17:06.058
That's not how it looks in the picture.

17:06.228 --> 17:08.526
Oh, yeah,
every bartender makes it differently.

17:08.697 --> 17:12.189
- Why don't you give it a try?
- All right.

17:13.702 --> 17:16.034
To the metric system.

17:26.481 --> 17:28.915
I can't taste the cherries.

17:30.752 --> 17:32.947
All right, Sheldon,
what's on your mind?

17:33.755 --> 17:36.781
I wronged Howard
and he won't accept my apology.

17:36.992 --> 17:38.050
Oh, right, that.

17:38.226 --> 17:40.194
Yes, Leonard told me. Sorry, honey.

17:40.762 --> 17:43.128
Penny,
you face failure on a daily basis.

17:45.467 --> 17:48.402
- How do you cope?
- I drink.

17:50.305 --> 17:52.000
To drinking.

17:55.110 --> 17:56.600
Nope.

18:00.115 --> 18:03.516
If only there were some way to
force Howard to accept my apology...

18:03.719 --> 18:06.347
...so I could escape
this miasma of guilt.

18:06.588 --> 18:09.921
Sometimes just stuff happens
and there's nothing you can do about it.

18:10.092 --> 18:13.255
For example, Lisa Peterson hasn't talked
to me since 11th grade.

18:13.428 --> 18:15.293
No matter how much you apologize...

18:15.464 --> 18:18.297
...you can't go back
and undry-hump someone's boyfriend.

18:19.434 --> 18:20.594
I see.

18:20.769 --> 18:23.704
You're saying I'm facing
Starfleet Academy's...

18:23.872 --> 18:27.239
...unwinnable command scenario:
The Kobayashi Maru.

18:27.442 --> 18:29.637
Exactly. Sometimes you can't win.

18:29.845 --> 18:31.972
Captain Kirk won.

18:33.281 --> 18:35.340
Kirk cheated.

18:36.518 --> 18:38.452
Impressive that you know that.

18:39.955 --> 18:43.356
Hard to believe I'm actually having
this conversation with you.

18:43.525 --> 18:45.550
Right there with you.

18:46.361 --> 18:51.663
Kirk beat the Kobayashi Maru
by reprogramming the simulator.

18:52.167 --> 18:53.498
- That's it.
- What?

18:53.702 --> 18:55.363
I'll reprogram Howard.

18:55.537 --> 18:58.836
Wait...
Sheldon, you can't reprogram people.

18:59.040 --> 19:01.634
No, you can't reprogram people.

19:02.911 --> 19:05.971
To James Tiberius Kirk.

19:15.824 --> 19:17.758
- Hello, all.
LEONARD: Hello.

19:17.926 --> 19:22.090
Howard, you're feeling better
about me today, aren't you?

19:22.330 --> 19:25.663
- Not really.
- Yes, you are.

19:25.834 --> 19:30.362
I'm using neuro-linguistic programming
to modify your thought patterns.

19:32.207 --> 19:34.175
Go away, Sheldon.

19:34.743 --> 19:37.405
There's a 9.95 eBook
down the drain.

19:38.013 --> 19:39.913
- What's in the bag?
- It's for Howard.

19:40.081 --> 19:42.914
No, Sheldon,
you can't fix this with gifts.

19:43.118 --> 19:46.383
Nevertheless, I've hurt you
and whether you forgive me or not...

19:46.588 --> 19:48.556
...I want you to have this.

19:50.625 --> 19:52.718
You're giving me a couch cushion?

19:52.894 --> 19:55.089
No. The cushion is merely symbolic.

19:55.263 --> 19:57.959
I'm giving you my spot on the couch.

20:00.569 --> 20:02.036
But you love that spot.

20:02.237 --> 20:04.467
No, I love my mother.

20:04.639 --> 20:08.439
My feelings for my spot
are much greater.

20:09.277 --> 20:14.442
It is the singular location in space around
which revolves my entire universe.

20:15.650 --> 20:17.117
And now it's yours.

20:18.153 --> 20:21.645
Oh, my God, dude,
now you have to forgive him.

20:23.091 --> 20:25.889
All right. Uh, apology accepted.

20:26.728 --> 20:28.059
High five.

20:28.230 --> 20:30.095
Not too hard.

20:31.433 --> 20:32.900
Thank you.

20:33.101 --> 20:36.366
I haven't cried like this
since Toy Story 3.

20:46.348 --> 20:49.476
I gotta tell you, Sheldon,
I understand why you chose this spot.

20:49.651 --> 20:52.484
I mean, the temperature's good,
but there's no draft.

20:52.654 --> 20:55.145
I can see the television,
but I can still talk to...

20:55.323 --> 20:57.348
I changed my mind.
Get out of my spot.

20:59.127 --> 21:02.722
- How long?
- Ninety-four seconds.

21:32.861 --> 21:34.852
[English - US - SDH]
